{
    "pages": [
        {
            "chapter": 56,
            "verse": 17,
            "text": "There will circulate among them, ageless youths"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 56,
            "verse": 18,
            "text": "carrying goblets and decanters and a cup from a flowing spring —"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 56,
            "verse": 19,
            "text": "it does not give them any headache nor does it leave them stupefied"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 56,
            "verse": 20,
            "text": "And any fruit they specify"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 56,
            "verse": 21,
            "text": "and any bird-meat they desire"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 56,
            "verse": 22,
            "text": "And dark-eyed maidens"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 56,
            "verse": 23,
            "text": "like hidden pearls"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 56,
            "verse": 24,
            "text": "As recompense for what they did"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 56,
            "verse": 25,
            "text": "They will hear no prattling in it nor any word of wrong"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 56,
            "verse": 26,
            "text": "All that is said is, ´Peace! Peace!´"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 56,
            "verse": 27,
            "text": "And the Companions of the Right: what of the Companions of the Right"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 56,
            "verse": 28,
            "text": "Amid thornless lote-trees"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 56,
            "verse": 29,
            "text": "and fruit-laden acacias"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 56,
            "verse": 30,
            "text": "and wide-spreading shade"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 56,
            "verse": 31,
            "text": "and outpouring water"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 56,
            "verse": 32,
            "text": "and fruits in abundance"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 56,
            "verse": 33,
            "text": "never failing, unrestricted"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 56,
            "verse": 34,
            "text": "And on elevated couches"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 56,
            "verse": 35,
            "text": "We have brought maidens into being"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 56,
            "verse": 36,
            "text": "and made them purest virgins"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 56,
            "verse": 37,
            "text": "devoted, passionate, of like age"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 56,
            "verse": 38,
            "text": "for the Companions of the Right"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 56,
            "verse": 39,
            "text": "A large group of the earlier people"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 56,
            "verse": 40,
            "text": "and a large group of the later ones"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 56,
            "verse": 41,
            "text": "And the Companions of the Left: what of the Companions of the Left"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 56,
            "verse": 42,
            "text": "Amid searing blasts and scalding water"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 56,
            "verse": 43,
            "text": "and the murk of thick black smoke"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 56,
            "verse": 44,
            "text": "providing no coolness and no pleasure"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 56,
            "verse": 45,
            "text": "Before that they were living in luxury"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 56,
            "verse": 46,
            "text": "persisting in immense wrongdoing"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 56,
            "verse": 47,
            "text": "and saying, ´When we are dead and turned to dust and bones, shall we then be raised again"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 56,
            "verse": 48,
            "text": "or our forefathers, the earlier peoples?´"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 56,
            "verse": 49,
            "text": "Say: ´The earlier and the later peoples will certainly all be gathered"
        },
        {
            "chapter": 56,
            "verse": 50,
            "text": "to the appointment of a specified Day"
        }
    ]
